==English==
====Etymology====
From ''[[phosphorus]]'' + ''[[-escent]]''

===Adjective===
'''phosphorescent'''
#Having the property of [[emit|emitting]] light for a period of time after the source of [[excitation]] is taken away, e.g., in [[electrostatic]] storage tubes and [[cathode-ray tube]]s.

====Derived terms====
*[[phosphorescence]]
*[[phosphorescently]]

